Facilities Use Agreement (SEGS IX) This Facilities Use Agreement (Agreement) is made and entered into as of July 22, 2022, by and between Luz Solar Partners Ltd., IX, a California limited partnership (Project Company), and Lockhart Transmission Holdings, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (GenTie Co). Project Company and GenTie Co may be referred to herein collectively as the Parties and individually as a Party. RECITALS WHEREAS, Project Company owns a solar-powered generation facility with an aggregate capacity of approximately 80 MW (the Facility) near Hinckley, California. WHEREAS, GenTie Co is owns the approximately 13.8-mile, double-circuit, 220 kV transmission line (the Transmission Line), which runs from the Facilitys switchyard (the Switchyard) to the Kramer Junction substation (the Substation). WHEREAS, GenTie Co and Project Company desire to enter into this Agreement to allow Project Company to use the Transmission Line to deliver the output of the Facility from the Switchyard to the Substation. NOW, THEREFORE, the parties hereto agree as follows: ARTICLE 1 DEFINITIONS For the purposes of this Agreement, the following words and terms shall have the meanings specified below: Affiliate means, with respect to any Person, any other Person that directly or indirectly, through one or more intermediaries, controls, is controlled by or is under common control with that Person. The term control (including with correlative meaning, the terms controlled by possession, directly or indirectly, of the power to direct or cause the direction of the management and under common control with), as used with respect to any Person, means the and policies of such Person, whether through the ownership of voting securities or membership or partnership interests, by contract or otherwise. Agreement has the meaning given in the preamble. Applicable Law means all laws, treaties, ordinances, statutes, judgments, injunctions, decrees, orders, writs, rules, regulations and interpretations of any Governmental Authority to the extent they apply to the actions of the Parties. CAISO means California Independent System Operator Corporation. Event of Default has the meaning set forth in Section 6.1 of the Agreement. Facility has the meaning given in the Recitals.
FERC means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. Financing Party means (i) any and all lenders providing senior or subordinated construction, interim or long-term debt financing or refinancing (including hedging counterparties) for the development, construction, purchase or operation of the Facility, and (ii) any and all equity or tax investors providing financing or refinancing of the Facility or purchasing equity ownership interests in a company owning the Project Company, including through a lease financing structure, and any trustee or agent acting on behalf of any such lenders, equity or tax investors, or lease equity providers. Force Majeure has the meaning set forth in Section 4.2 of the Agreement. Governmental Authority means any national, state or local government, any political subdivision thereof, or any governmental, quasi-governmental, judicial, public or statutory instrumentality, administrative agency, authority, body or other entity having jurisdiction over a Partys operations, or over the Parties. Indemnified Party has the meaning set forth Section 5.1 of the Agreement. Indemnifying Party has the meaning set forth Section 5.1 of the Agreement. LGIA means any agreement for the interconnection of the Facility. Mortgage has the meaning set forth in Section 7.3 of this Agreement. O&M Agreements means any agreement between GenTie Co and any third party (including Terra-Gen Operating Company, LLC, or its successors and assigns), which will provide operation and maintenance services to GenTie Co with respect to the Transmission Line. Person means any individual, corporation, partnership, limited liability company, association, joint stock company, trust, unincorporated organization, joint venture, government or political subdivision or agency therefore, Governmental Authority, or any other entity or organization. Project Company has the meaning given in the preamble. Prudent Utility Practices means those practices, methods, standards and acts engaged in or approved by a significant portion of the electric industry during the relevant time period, or any of the practices, methods and acts which, in the exercise of reasonable judgment in light of the facts known at the time the decision was made, could have been expected to accomplish the desired result at a reasonable cost consistent with good business practices, reliability, safety and expedition in a manner consistent with Applicable Laws, safety, environmental protection and economy. Prudent Utility Practices are not necessarily defined as the optimal standard practice method or act to the exclusion of others, but rather refer to a range of action reasonable under the circumstances and generally accepted in the region in connection with line taps and the ownership and operation of the facilities and arrangements described in this Agreement. Substation means the meaning given in the Recitals. - 2 - Switchyard means the meaning given in the Recitals. Transmission Line has the meaning given in the Recitals.
ARTICLE 2 USE OF FACILITIES 2.1 Connection. GenTie Co will allow Project Company to connect the Facility to the Transmission Line and will cooperate with Project Company to effectuate such connection in accordance with Applicable Laws and Prudent Utility Practice. 2.2 Use of the Transmission Line. During the term of this Agreement, GenTie Co will allow Project Company to use the Transmission Line to deliver the output of the Facility from the Switchyard to the Substation and to deliver electricity from a provider of station service from the Substation to the Switchyard. Project Companys right to use the Transmission Line shall be limited to the capacity of the Facility set forth in the recitals hereto. Project Companys right to use the Transmission Line is contingent on its ownership interest in GenTie Co. If Project Company transfers a portion of its ownership interest in GenTie Co, then its rights to use the Transmission Line shall be reduced to a capacity equal to the number of Units (as defined in the LLC operating agreement of GenTie Co) retained by Project Company in GenTie Co. 2.3 Scheduling. No scheduling services are required for the service provided under this Agreement. Project Company shall make all necessary scheduling arrangements with Southern California Edison Company and/or the CAISO to accept Project Companys output at the Substation. 2.4 Availability. GenTie Co acknowledges that Project Companys rights to access and utilize the Transmission Line is essential to the administration, operation and maintenance of the Facility. GenTie Co shall comply at all times with the requirements of this Agreement, shall operate and maintain its Transmission Line in accordance with Prudent Utility Practices, and coordinate any outages as follows: (a) coordinate with the other Parties with respect to scheduling any planned outages of the its Transmission Line with the goal of scheduling planned outages during periods which minimize the impact on Project Companys operations. (b) shall give notice to the other Parties as soon as possible of any unplanned outages of its Transmission Line and shall work to restore its Transmission Line to service as quickly as possible. 2.5 Curtailment. Project Companys use of the Transmission Line may be subject to curtailment to the extent necessary to maintain reliable operation of the Transmission Line or the transmission systems directly and indirectly interconnected with the Transmission Line. When GenTie Co determines, in its sole discretion, that an electrical emergency exists on its Transmission Line and implements emergency procedures to curtail use of the Transmission Line pursuant to the GenTie Cos LLC operating agreement, Project Company shall make the required reductions upon the request of GenTie Co in accordance with Prudent Utility Practices. GenTie - 3 - Co will provide Project Company with advance notice of curtailment where such notice can be provided consistent with Prudent Utility Practices. 2.6 Ancillary Services. Project Company shall be responsible for procuring or self- supplying electricity necessary for the operation of the Facility and any other ancillary services necessary to support the transmission of energy over the Transmission Line while maintaining reliable operation of the Transmission Line in accordance with Prudent Utility Practices. 2.7 Line Losses. Project Company shall be responsible for its line losses on the Transmission Line. 2.8 Charges. Project Company shall reimburse GenTie Co for: (a) all expenses necessary for the operation and maintenance of its Transmission Line, including, but not limited to: (i) all fees and expenses payable under the applicable O&M Agreement; (ii) insurance expenses; (iii) property or other ad valorem taxes assessed or allocated to its Transmission Line; and (iv) the costs of licenses and permits; and (b) any annual charges GenTie Co may be required to pay to FERC pursuant to 18 C.F.R. 382.201 as a result of providing service to Project Company under this Agreement. Notwithstanding the foregoing, in no event shall Project Company be responsible for more than its share of expenses due under the LLC operating agreement of GenTie Co. ARTICLE 3-- TERM AND TERMINATION 3.1 Term. Service under this Agreement shall commence upon receipt of all regulatory approvals for GenTieCo to own the Transmission Line, and shall continue in effect until terminated by (a) mutual agreement of the Parties or (b) pursuant to Section 3.2 or 6.1(b). 3.2 Termination. This Agreement shall terminate (i) upon the date that Project Company, or its successors and assigns, have permanently ceased operation of the Facility for the production of energy, or (ii) if Project Company transfers all of its ownership interest in GenTie Co, and this Agreement is not assigned in accordance with Section 7.1. 3.3 Governmental Approvals for Termination. Notwithstanding anything in this Agreement to the contrary, termination shall not become effective until the Parties have complied with all Applicable Laws applicable to such termination, including obtaining any necessary FERC authorizations for such termination. 3.4 Survival Rights. Termination of this Agreement (a) shall not relieve any Party of any obligation hereunder which expressly or by implication survives termination hereof, including all indemnity obligations, and (b) except as otherwise provided in any provision of this Agreement expressly limiting the liability of a Party, shall not relieve a Party of any obligations or liabilities for loss or damage to the other Parties arising out of or caused by any breach of this Agreement by such Party prior to the effectiveness of such termination or arising out of such termination. - 4 - ARTICLE 4-- FORCE MAJEURE 4.1 Excuse. No Party shall be considered in default under this Agreement for any delay or failure in the performance of its obligations and shall be excused in the performance of its obligations under this Agreement if such delay or failure is due to an event of Force Majeure. 4.2 Definition. Force Majeure means any event or circumstance, including any of the following enumerated events, that occur before the termination of this Agreement and that delays or prevents a Partys performance of its obligations under this Agreement, but only to the extent that (a) such event of Force Majeure is not attributable to fault or negligence on the part of such Party, (b) such event of Force Majeure is caused by factors beyond such Partys reasonable control; and (c) despite taking all reasonable technical and commercial precautions and measures to prevent, avoid, mitigate or overcome such event and the consequences thereof, such Party affected has been unable to prevent, avoid, mitigate or overcome such event or consequences: (a) Acts of God such as epidemic, pandemic, storms, hurricanes, floods, lightning and earthquakes; (b) Sabotage or destruction by a third-party of facilities and equipment relating to the performance by the affected Party of its obligations under this Agreement; (c) War, riot, acts of a public enemy or other civil disturbance; (d) Strike, walkout, lockout or other significant labor dispute; or (e) Action or inaction of a Governmental Authority. 4.3 Conditions. A Party may rely on a claim of Force Majeure to excuse its performance only to the extent that such Party: (a) Provides prompt notice of such Force Majeure event to the other Parties, giving an estimate of its expected duration and the probable impact on the performance of its obligations under this Agreement; (b) Exercises all reasonable efforts to continue to perform its obligations under this Agreement; (c) Expeditiously takes action to correct or cure the event or condition excusing performance so that the suspension of performance is no greater in scope and no longer in duration than is dictated by the event or condition being corrected or cured using commercially reasonable efforts; provided, however, that settlement of strikes or other labor disputes will be completely within the sole discretion of the Party affected by such strike or labor dispute; (d) Exercises all commercially reasonable efforts to mitigate or limit damages to the other Parties; and (e) Provides prompt notice to the other Parties of the cessation of the event or condition giving rise to its excuse from performance. - 5 - ARTICLE 5-- INDEMNIFICATION 5.1 General Indemnity. Each Party (the Indemnifying Party) shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless the other Party and their directors, managers, officers, agents, employees, successors and assigns (each, an Indemnified Party) from and against any and all suits, actions, legal or administrative proceedings, claims, demands, costs (including reasonable attorneys fees) and expenses (each a Claim) of any nature for death or personal injury to any person or physical damage to the property of third parties arising from (i) a negligent (whether active or passive) act or omission or the willful misconduct of the Indemnifying Party, or its contractors, or their respective employees or agents; or (ii) any failure of the Indemnifying Party to comply with Applicable Law in connection with this Agreement; except to the extent such Claim arise from the negligence or willful misconduct of an Indemnified Party. 5.2 Indemnification Procedure. When required to indemnify an Indemnified Party, the Indemnifying Party shall assume on behalf of such Indemnified Party and conduct with due diligence and in good faith the defense of any Claim against such party, whether or not the Indemnifying Party shall be joined therein, and the Indemnified Party shall cooperate with the Indemnifying Party in such defense. The Indemnifying Party shall have charge and direction of the defense and settlement of such Claim; provided, however, that without relieving the Indemnifying Party of its obligations hereunder or impairing the Indemnifying Partys right to control the defense or settlement thereof, the Indemnified Party may elect to participate through separate counsel in the defense of any such Claim, but the fees and expenses of such counsel shall be at the expense of such Indemnified Party unless (a) the counsel employed by such Indemnified Party shall have reasonably concluded that there exists a material conflict of interest between the Indemnifying Party and such Indemnified Party in the conduct of the defense of such Claim (in which case the Indemnifying Party shall not have the right to control the defense or settlement of such claim on behalf of such Indemnified Party), or (b) the Indemnifying Party shall not have employed counsel to assume the defense of such Claim within a reasonable time after notice of the commencement thereof. In each of such cases the fees and expenses of counsel shall be at the expense of the Indemnifying Party. ARTICLE 6-- TERMINATION FOR DEFAULT 6.1 Event of Default (a) A Party shall be in default under this Agreement (an Event of Default) if such Party fails to perform in any material respect any of its obligations under this Agreement or the GenTie Co LLC operating agreement. (b) A Party may terminate this Agreement upon an Event of Default by another Party (i) if such Event of Default is not cured within thirty (30) days after receipt of such Partys written notice to the defaulting Party, or (ii) if such Event of Default is not a payment default and can be cured but not within the aforesaid thirty (30) day period, corrective action is not commenced within thirty (30) days after receipt of such Partys written notice to the defaulting Party and the defaulting Party does not thereafter diligently pursue such cure and complete the cure within a reasonable period of time. - 6 - (c) Consequences of Termination. Upon termination by a Party for an Event of Default, each non-defaulting Party shall be entitled to all legal and equitable remedies that are not expressly prohibited or limited by the terms of this Agreement. ARTICLE 7 ASSIGNMENTS AND TRANSFERS 7.1 Project Company. Project Company shall not transfer or assign this Agreement; provided, however, that Project Company shall have the right to assign this Agreement (i) if a transfer of Project Companys interest in GenTie Co is permitted by the LLC operating agreement of GenTie Co, and (ii) such assignment of this Agreement is accompanied by an assignment of Project Companys interest in GenTie Co. When duly assigned in accordance with the foregoing, this Agreement shall be binding upon and shall inure to the benefit of the assignee; any other assignment shall be void and without force or effect. 7.2 GenTie Company. GenTie Co shall not transfer, sell, assign or sublease the Agreement or its ownership interest in the Agreement or Transmission Line without the prior written consent of Project Company; any other assignment shall be void and without force or effect. 7.3 Project Companys Right to Encumber. Notwithstanding anything in Section 7.1 to the contrary, Project Company may, at any time and from time to time during the term of this Agreement, encumber, mortgage or hypothecate to any Financing Party by a security or similar agreement, (the Mortgage) all or part of Project Companys interest under this Agreement and the other documents entered into in connection with this Agreement, including, without limitation, the LGIA, without the consent of the other Parties hereto. Should Project Company incur any encumbrance in accordance with this Section 7.3, and should the Parties receive notice thereof, the Parties hereby expressly stipulate and agree between themselves and on behalf of, and for the benefit of, the Financing Party as follows: (a) Modification of Agreement. They will not modify this Agreement or allow this Agreement to be modified in any way nor cancel this Agreement without the written consent of the Financing Party, which consent may not be unreasonably withheld or delayed. (b) Performance by Financing Party. The Financing Party shall have the right to do any act or thing required of the Project Company under this Agreement, and any such act or thing performed by the Financing Party shall be as effective to prevent a default under this Agreement and/or a forfeiture of any of Project Companys rights under this Agreement as if done by the Project Company itself, provided that the Financing Party shall have first given the Project Company such notice and allowed the Project Company to perform or attempt to perform such act or thing for such period of time as may be specified in any documents or instruments executed by the Project Company for the benefit of the Financing Party. The Financing Party shall have such foreclosure and sale rights and rights to perform or cause to be performed the covenants and agreements of the Project Company under this Agreement as may be specified in any documents or instruments executed by the Project Company for the benefit of the Financing Party. - 7 - (c) Notice to Financing Party. If any GenTie Company issues or receives any notices regarding potential or actual defaults as described herein, GenTie Company shall as soon as practicable deliver a copy of such notice to all Financing Parties of which it has received notice. (d) Consents to Assignment. GenTie Company hereby agrees that it shall, no later than five (5) business days after a request by the Project Company (or its Financing Party), execute such consents or estoppel certificates as are reasonably requested by the Project Company or its Financing Party. ARTICLE 8 REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES 8.1 GenTie Co Representations. GenTie Co represents and warrants that: (a) Organization. GenTie Co is a limited liability company duly organized, validly existing and in good standing under the laws of the State of Delaware, and is qualified to do business in all jurisdictions in which the nature of the business conducted by it makes such qualification necessary and where failure to so qualify would have a material adverse effect on its ability to perform this Agreement. (b) No Violation of Law; Litigation. GenTie Co is not in violation of any Applicable Laws, or judgment entered by any Governmental Authority which violations, individually or in the aggregate, would materially and adversely affect its performance of any obligations under this Agreement. (c) Company Action. GenTie Co has all necessary power and authority to execute, deliver and perform its obligations under this Agreement; the execution, delivery and performance by GenTie Co of this Agreement have been duly authorized by all necessary limited liability company action on its part; and, this Agreement has been duly and validly executed and delivered by GenTie Co and constitutes the legal, valid and binding obligation of GenTie Co enforceable in accordance with its terms, except as the enforceability thereof may be limited by bankruptcy, insolvency, reorganization or moratorium or other similar laws relating to the enforcement of creditors rights generally and by general equitable principles. 8.2 Project Company Representations. Project Company represents and warrants that: (a) Organization. Project Company is a limited liability company duly organized, validly existing and in good standing under the laws of the State of Delaware, and is qualified to do business in all jurisdictions in which the nature of the business conducted by it makes such qualification necessary and where failure to so qualify would have a material adverse effect on its ability to perform this Agreement. (b) No Violation of Law; Litigation. Project Company is not in violation of any Applicable Laws or judgment entered by any Governmental Authority, which violations, individually or in the aggregate, would materially and adversely affect its performance of any obligations under this Agreement. - 8 - (c) Company Action. Project Company has all necessary power and authority to execute, deliver and perform its obligations under this Agreement; the execution, delivery and performance by Project Company of this Agreement have been duly authorized by all necessary action on its part; and, this Agreement has been duly and validly executed and delivered by Project Company and constitutes the legal, valid and binding obligation of Project Company enforceable in accordance with its terms, except as the enforceability thereof may be limited by bankruptcy, insolvency, reorganization or moratorium or other similar laws relating to the enforcement of creditors rights generally and by general equitable principles. This Agreement is governed by the laws of the State of California, excluding any choice of law rules that would direct application of laws of another jurisdiction. Each Party hereby irrevocably and unconditionally submits to the exclusive jurisdiction of any California State court or federal court of the United States of America sitting in Los Angeles, and waives, to the fullest extent legally permissible, any objection which it may now or hereafter have to the personal jurisdiction of such courts or venue of any proceeding arising out of or relating to this Agreement in such courts and any defense of an inconvenient forum to the maintenance of such action or proceeding in such courts. 9.2 Jury Trial Waiver. FOR AVOIDANCE OF DOUBT, LOST REVENUES FROM LOST PRODUCTION OR PRODUCTION RESULTING FROM AN OUTAGE, DISCONNECTION, OR DAMAGE TO A PROJECT SHALL NOT BE CONSIDERED CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES HEREUNDER, AND SHALL BE FULLY RECOVERABLE DAMAGES FOR ANY CLAIMS ARISING HEREUNDER. 10.2 Releases Valid in All Events. Releases, disclaimers and limitations on liability expressed herein shall apply even in the event of the negligence, strict liability, fault or breach of contract (including other legal bases of responsibility such as fundamental breach) of the Party whose liability is released, disclaimed or limited to the extent provided in such release, disclaimer and limitation and shall inure to the benefit of the released Partys Affiliates. - 9 - ARTICLE 11 GENERAL PROVISIONS 11.1 Notices. Any notice required or authorized to be given hereunder or any other communications between the Parties shall be in writing (unless otherwise provided) and shall be served personally or by reputable express courier service or by facsimile transmission addressed to the relevant Party at the address stated below or at any other address notified by such Party to the other Parties as its address for service. Any notice so given personally shall be deemed to have been served on delivery, any notice so given by express courier service shall be deemed to have been served two (2) working days after the same shall have been delivered to the relevant courier, and any notice so given by facsimile transmission shall be deemed to have been served on dispatch; provided that such facsimile notice is transmitted during business hours in the primary recipients location (which, for purposes of this Section 11.1, shall mean any time before 5:00 p.m. on a day that is not a Saturday, Sunday or legal holiday in the state where such recipient is located) and otherwise shall be deemed to have been served upon the commencement of the next succeeding business hours in the recipients location. As proof of such service it shall be sufficient to produce a receipt showing personal service, the receipt of a reputable courier company showing the correct address of the addressee or an activity report of the senders facsimile machine showing the correct facsimile number of the Party on whom notice is served and the correct number of pages transmitted and the date of dispatch. The Parties addresses for service are as follows, although each Party may change its address for service by written notice to the other Parties given as provided in this Section 11.1: If to Project Company: c/o Terra-Gen, LLC nd 437 Madison Ave., 22 Floor New York, NY 10022 Attention: Chief Financial Officer If to GenTie Co: c/o Terra-Gen, LLC nd 437 Madison Ave., 22 Floor New York, NY 10022 Attention: Senior Vice President - Operations 11.2 Change of Notice Recipient Information. Any Party may, by giving notice at any time or from time to time, require subsequent notice to be given to another individual, whether a Party or an officer or representative of a Party, or to a different address, or both. Notices given before actual receipt of notice of change shall not be invalidated by the change. 11.3 Amendment. This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement among the parties pertaining to the subject matter hereof and supersedes all prior agreements, representations, communications and understandings, written or oral, express or implied, pertaining thereto. Any changes to this Agreement shall require the written approval of the Parties (not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed) and the Financing Party pursuant to Section 7.3(a) and shall be subject to FERC approval; provided, however, that, in the event that Project Company is no longer the sole - 10 - customer using the Transmission Line, GenTie Company shall revise Section 2.8(b) to reflect a pro rata allocation of such costs and timely make any required filings with FERC with respect to such amendment. 11.4 Construction. The language in all parts of this Agreement shall be in all cases construed simply according to its fair meaning and not strictly for or against any of the Parties hereto. 11.5 Validity. Should any portion of this Agreement be declared invalid and unenforceable, then such portion shall be deemed to be severable from this Agreement and shall not affect the remainder hereof; and the Parties shall negotiate in good faith to replace such invalid and unenforceable provision. 11.6 Waiver. The failure of a Party at any time to require performance by another Party of any provision hereof shall not affect in any way the full right to require such performance at any time thereafter, nor shall the waiver by a Party of any breach of any provision hereof be held or deemed to be a waiver of the provision itself. 11.7 Third-Party Beneficiaries. Except for provisions (including indemnity, limitation of liability, waiver and release provisions) that are expressly stated as inuring for the benefit of a Partys Affiliates or its directors, managers, officers, agents, employees, successors and assigns, the provisions of this Agreement are intended for the sole benefit of Project Company, the Financing Party and GenTie Co, and there are no third-party beneficiaries other than assignees contemplated by the terms herein. 11.8 Further Assurances. Each Party agrees to provide such information, execute and deliver any instruments and documents and take such other actions as may be necessary or reasonably requested by another Party that are not inconsistent with the provisions of this Agreement and that do not involve the assumption of obligations other than those provided for in this Agreement, in order to give full effect to this Agreement and to carry out the intent of this Agreement. 11.9 Counterparts. This Agreement may be executed in any number of counterparts and by each of the Parties in separate counterparts, each of which when so executed shall be deemed to be an original and all of which taken together shall constitute one and the same Agreement.

Facilities Use Agreement (Lockhart PV and CL BESS I; Transmission Line) This Second Amended and Restated Facilities Use Agreement (Agreement) is made and entered into as of June 28, 2024, by and among Lockhart Solar PV, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (PV ProjectCo), Lockhart CL ESS I, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (CL BESS ProjectCo, and together with PV ProjectCo, each a ProjectCo, and collectively, the ProjectCos) and Lockhart Transmission Holdings, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (GenTie Co). PV ProjectCo, CL BESS ProjectCo and GenTie Co may be referred to herein collectively as the Parties and individually as a Party. RECITALS WHEREAS, PV ProjectCo owns a solar-powered generation facility with an aggregate capacity of approximately 85 MW (the PV Facility) near Hinckley, California. WHEREAS, CL BESS ProjectCo is developing a battery energy storage system with an aggregate capacity of approximately 69 MW (the BESS Facility) near Hinckley, California. WHEREAS, GenTie Co owns the approximately 13.8-mile, double-circuit, 220 kV transmission line (the Transmission Line), which runs from the switchyard shared by the PV Facility and the BESS Facility (the Switchyard) to the Kramer Junction substation (the Substation). WHEREAS, PV ProjectCo and GenTieCo executed an Amended and Restated Facility Use Agreement on February 7, 2023 (the Original Agreement), and as a result of the assignment by PV ProjectCo to CL BESS ProjectCo of rights to use the BESS Capacity on the Transmission Line, the Parties now desire to terminate the Original Agreement and enter into this Agreement to allow PV ProjectCo and CL BESS ProjectCo to share the use of their combined interconnection capacity (Coincident Capacity) to use the Transmission Line to deliver the output of the PV Facility and the CL BESS Facility from the Switchyard to the Substation. NOW, THEREFORE, the parties hereto agree as follows: ARTICLE 1 DEFINITIONS For the purposes of this Agreement, the following words and terms shall have the meanings specified below: Affiliate means, with respect to any Person, any other Person that directly or indirectly, through one or more intermediaries, controls, is controlled by or is under common control with that Person. The term control (including with correlative meaning, the terms controlled by possession, directly or indirectly, of the power to direct or cause the direction of the management and under common control with), as used with respect to any Person, means the and policies of such Person, whether through the ownership of voting securities or membership or partnership interests, by contract or otherwise.
Agreement has the meaning given in the preamble. Applicable Law means all laws, treaties, ordinances, statutes, judgments, injunctions, decrees, orders, writs, rules, regulations and interpretations of any Governmental Authority to the extent they apply to the actions of the Parties. "BESS Capacity means the interconnection use rights of CL BESS ProjectCo to use the Transmission Line to deliver the net output of the BESS Facility to the Point of Interconnection pursuant to the LGIA to the extent that the PV Facility is not capable of producing and delivering energy to the Point of Interconnection. BESS Capacity shall include all Deliverability rights and obligations as set forth in the LGIA. BESS Capacity may be referenced as Surplus Interconnection Service under relevant FERC orders. BESS Facility has the meaning given in the Recitals. CAISO means California Independent System Operator Corporation. CL BESS ProjectCo has the meaning given in the preamble. Coincident Capacity has the meaning given in the Recitals. Event of Default has the meaning set forth in Section 6.1 of the Agreement. Facility means the PV Facility or the BESS Facility, as appropriate. FERC means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. Financing Party means (i) any and all lenders providing senior or subordinated construction, interim or long-term debt financing or refinancing (including hedging counterparties) for the development, construction, purchase or operation of a Facility, and (ii) any and all equity or tax investors providing financing or refinancing of a Facility or purchasing equity ownership interests in a company owning a ProjectCo, including through a lease financing structure, and any trustee or agent acting on behalf of any such lenders, equity or tax investors, or lease equity providers. Force Majeure has the meaning set forth in Section 4.2 of the Agreement. GenTie Co has the meaning given in the preamble. GenTie Co LLCA means that certain Third Amended and Restated Limited Liability Company Agreement of Lockhart Transmission Holdings, LLC dated June 28, 2024, by and among PV ProjectCo, CL BESS ProjectCo, Lockhart Solar PV II, LLC, Lockhart CL ESS II, LLC, Lockhart ESS, LLC, Luz Solar Partners Ltd. IX, Lockhart Reserve, LLC and Terra-Gen Operating Company, LLC, as may be amended or updated from time to time. Governmental Authority means any national, state or local government, any political subdivision thereof, or any governmental, quasi-governmental, judicial, public or statutory - 2 - instrumentality, administrative agency, authority, body or other entity having jurisdiction over a Partys operations, or over the Parties. Indemnified Party has the meaning set forth Section 5.1 of the Agreement. Indemnifying Party has the meaning set forth Section 5.1 of the Agreement. LGIA means any agreement for the interconnection of the PV Facility. Mortgage has the meaning set forth in Section 7.3 of this Agreement. NERC means the North American Electric Reliability Corporation and the applicable regional reliability entity designated by NERC. Person means any individual, corporation, partnership, limited liability company, association, joint stock company, trust, unincorporated organization, joint venture, government or political subdivision or agency therefore, Governmental Authority, or any other entity or organization. ProjectCo has the meaning given in the preamble. Prudent Utility Practices means those practices, methods, standards and acts engaged in or approved by a significant portion of the electric industry during the relevant time period, or any of the practices, methods and acts which, in the exercise of reasonable judgment in light of the facts known at the time the decision was made, could have been expected to accomplish the desired result at a reasonable cost consistent with good business practices, reliability, safety and expedition in a manner consistent with Applicable Laws, safety, environmental protection and economy. Prudent Utility Practices are not necessarily defined as the optimal standard practice method or act to the exclusion of others, but rather refer to a range of action reasonable under the circumstances and generally accepted in the region in connection with line taps and the ownership and operation of the facilities and arrangements described in this Agreement. PV Capacity means the interconnection use rights of the PV ProjectCo to use the Transmission Line to deliver the net output of the PV Facility to the Point of Interconnection pursuant to the LGIA, and other ancillary interconnection needs related to 24x7 auxiliary power, facility communications and other requirements necessary for performance under the LGIA, to the extent that the PV Facility is capable of producing and delivering energy to the Point of Interconnection. PV Capacity shall not include charging or delivery of battery stored energy. PV Capacity shall not include Deliverability rights and obligations as set forth in the LGIA. PV Facility has the meaning given in the Recitals. PV ProjectCo has the meaning given in the preamble. SCE means the Southern California Edison Company. Substation means the meaning given in the Recitals. - 3 - Switchyard means the meaning given in the Recitals. Transmission Line has the meaning given in the Recitals.
ARTICLE 2 USE OF FACILITIES 2.1 Connection. GenTie Co will allow each ProjectCo to connect its Facility to the Transmission Line and will cooperate with each ProjectCo to effectuate such connection in accordance with Applicable Laws and Prudent Utility Practice. 2.2 Use of the Transmission Line. During the term of this Agreement, GenTie Co will allow each ProjectCo to use the Coincident Capacity of the Transmission Line to deliver the output of its Facility from the Switchyard to the Substation and to deliver electricity from a provider of station service from the Substation to the Switchyard. PV ProjectCos right to use the Transmission Line shall be limited to the PV Capacity of the PV Facility set forth in the recitals hereto. CL BESS ProjectCos right to use the Transmission Line shall be limited to the BESS Capacity of the BESS Facility set forth in the recitals hereto. Each ProjectCos right to use the Transmission Line is contingent on its ownership interest in GenTie Co. If a ProjectCo transfers a portion of its ownership interest in GenTie Co, then its rights to use the Transmission Line shall be reduced to a capacity equal to the number of Units (as defined in the GenTie Co LLCA) retained by such ProjectCo in GenTie Co. 2.3 Scheduling. No scheduling services are required for the service provided under this Agreement. Each ProjectCo shall make all necessary scheduling arrangements with Southern California Edison Company and/or the CAISO to accept its output at the Substation. 2.4 Availability. GenTie Co acknowledges that each ProjectCos rights to access and utilize its Coincident Capacity is essential to the administration, operation and maintenance of its Facility. GenTie Co shall comply at all times with the requirements of this Agreement, shall operate and maintain its Transmission Line in accordance with Prudent Utility Practices, and coordinate use of the Transmission Line and any outages as follows: (a) coordinate with the other Parties with respect to scheduling any planned outages of either Facility and the Transmission Line with the goal of scheduling planned outages during periods which minimize the impact on each Facilitys operations. (b) shall give notice to the other Parties as soon as possible of any unplanned outages of the Transmission Line and shall work to restore the Transmission Line to service as quickly as possible. (c) The ProjectCos shall adopt operating assumptions (the Operating Assumptions) that reflect the proposed charging and discharge behavior of the CL BESS ProjectCo in a manner that is consistent with its BESS Capacity, the terms and conditions of the LGIA, and the requirements and guidelines of CAISO, SCE, NERC and any other entity with authority over the operations of the ProjectCos. If required under the LGIA or by SCE or CAISO, the ProjectCos shall provide such Operating Assumptions to SCE and CAISO. For the - 4 - avoidance of doubt, the ProjectCos may operate at the same time, with the PV ProjectCo having priority pursuant to the terms set forth in the GenTieCo LLCA. (d) The ProjectCos shall direct any third-party providing operations and maintenance, scheduling or other services to perform in a manner consistent with the Operating Assumptions and the terms of this Agreement, including under any offtake agreement in which the offtaker controls the scheduling of the resource. (e) The CL BESS ProjectCo may use the Transmission Line to charge BESS Facility at any time without any limitation under this Agreement; provided, however, that the CL BESS ProjectCo shall limit its charging activities in accordance with the LGIA and the requirements and guidelines of CAISO, SCE, NERC and any other entity with authority over its operations. (f) The ProjectCos anticipate that the CL BESS ProjectCo will not often use the Transmission Line to discharge the BESS Facility in a manner that would cause the PV ProjectCo to curtail the PV Facility; provided, however, that: (i) no ProjectCo shall be obligated to take any action that could result in a violation of a CAISO or SCE tariff; (ii) each ProjectCo shall operate its Facility in accordance with all dispatch orders issued by the CAISO; (iii) the Parties acknowledge and agree that BESS Capacity includes Deliverability rights under the LGIA, which may result in CAISO directing the CL BESS ProjectCo to discharge the BESS Facility despite the PV ProjectCos rights to use its PV Capacity during such CAISO direction; and (iv) the CL BESS ProjectCo shall reimburse the PV ProjectCo for lost revenue and production tax credits as set forth in the GenTie Co LLCA. 2.5 Curtailment. Each ProjectCos use of the Coincident Capacity of the Transmission Line may be subject to curtailment to the extent necessary to maintain reliable operation of the Transmission Line or the transmission systems directly and indirectly interconnected with the Transmission Line. Each ProjectCo shall reimburse GenTie Co for its share of: (a) all expenses necessary for the operation and maintenance of its Transmission Line; and - 5 - (b) any annual charges GenTie Co may be required to pay to FERC pursuant to § 18 C.F.R. 382.201 as a result of providing service to each ProjectCo under this Agreement. Facilities Use Agreement (Lockhart PV II and CL BESS II; Transmission Line) This Second Amended and Restated Facilities Use Agreement (Agreement) is made and entered into as of June 28, 2024, by and among Lockhart Solar PV II LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (PV ProjectCo), Lockhart CL ESS II, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (CL BESS ProjectCo, and together with PV ProjectCo, each a ProjectCo, and collectively, the ProjectCos) and Lockhart Transmission Holdings, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (GenTie Co). PV ProjectCo, CL BESS ProjectCo and GenTie Co may be referred to herein collectively as the Parties and individually as a Party. RECITALS WHEREAS, PV ProjectCo owns a solar-powered generation facility with an aggregate capacity of approximately 75 MW (the PV Facility) near Hinckley, California. WHEREAS, CL BESS ProjectCo is developing a battery energy storage system with an aggregate capacity of approximately 59.7 MW (the BESS Facility) near Hinckley, California. WHEREAS, GenTie Co owns the approximately 13.8-mile, double-circuit, 220 kV transmission line (the Transmission Line), which runs from the switchyard shared by the PV Facility and the BESS Facility (the Switchyard) to the Kramer Junction substation (the Substation). WHEREAS, PV ProjectCo and GenTieCo executed an Amended and Restated Facility Use Agreement on February 7, 2023 (the Original Agreement), and as a result of the assignment by PV ProjectCo to CL BESS ProjectCo of rights to use the BESS Capacity on the Transmission Line, the Parties now desire to terminate the Original Agreement and enter into this Agreement to allow PV ProjectCo and CL BESS ProjectCo to share the use of their combined interconnection capacity (Coincident Capacity) to use the Transmission Line to deliver the output of the PV Facility and the CL BESS Facility from the Switchyard to the Substation. NOW, THEREFORE, the parties hereto agree as follows: ARTICLE 1 DEFINITIONS For the purposes of this Agreement, the following words and terms shall have the meanings specified below: Affiliate means, with respect to any Person, any other Person that directly or indirectly, through one or more intermediaries, controls, is controlled by or is under common control with that Person. The term control (including with correlative meaning, the terms controlled by possession, directly or indirectly, of the power to direct or cause the direction of the management and under common control with), as used with respect to any Person, means the and policies of such Person, whether through the ownership of voting securities or membership or partnership interests, by contract or otherwise.
Agreement has the meaning given in the preamble. Applicable Law means all laws, treaties, ordinances, statutes, judgments, injunctions, decrees, orders, writs, rules, regulations and interpretations of any Governmental Authority to the extent they apply to the actions of the Parties. "BESS Capacity means the interconnection use rights of CL BESS ProjectCo to use the Transmission Line to deliver the net output of the BESS Facility to the Point of Interconnection pursuant to the LGIA to the extent that the PV Facility is not capable of producing and delivering energy to the Point of Interconnection. BESS Capacity shall include all Deliverability rights and obligations as set forth in the LGIA. BESS Capacity may be referenced as Surplus Interconnection Service under relevant FERC orders. BESS Facility has the meaning given in the Recitals. CAISO means California Independent System Operator Corporation. CL BESS ProjectCo has the meaning given in the preamble. Coincident Capacity has the meaning given in the Recitals. Event of Default has the meaning set forth in Section 6.1 of the Agreement. Facility means the PV Facility or the BESS Facility, as appropriate. FERC means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. Financing Party means (i) any and all lenders providing senior or subordinated construction, interim or long-term debt financing or refinancing (including hedging counterparties) for the development, construction, purchase or operation of a Facility, and (ii) any and all equity or tax investors providing financing or refinancing of a Facility or purchasing equity ownership interests in a company owning a ProjectCo, including through a lease financing structure, and any trustee or agent acting on behalf of any such lenders, equity or tax investors, or lease equity providers. Force Majeure has the meaning set forth in Section 4.2 of the Agreement. GenTie Co has the meaning given in the preamble. GenTie Co LLCA means that certain Third Amended and Restated Limited Liability Company Agreement of Lockhart Transmission Holdings, LLC dated June 28, 2024, by and among PV ProjectCo, CL BESS ProjectCo, Lockhart Solar PV, LLC, Lockhart CL ESS I, LLC, Lockhart ESS, LLC, Luz Solar Partners Ltd. IX, Lockhart Reserve, LLC and Terra-Gen Operating Company, LLC, as may be amended or updated from time to time. Governmental Authority means any national, state or local government, any political subdivision thereof, or any governmental, quasi-governmental, judicial, public or statutory - 2 - instrumentality, administrative agency, authority, body or other entity having jurisdiction over a Partys operations, or over the Parties. Indemnified Party has the meaning set forth Section 5.1 of the Agreement. Indemnifying Party has the meaning set forth Section 5.1 of the Agreement. LGIA means any agreement for the interconnection of the PV Facility. Mortgage has the meaning set forth in Section 7.3 of this Agreement. NERC means the North American Electric Reliability Corporation and the applicable regional reliability entity designated by NERC. Person means any individual, corporation, partnership, limited liability company, association, joint stock company, trust, unincorporated organization, joint venture, government or political subdivision or agency therefore, Governmental Authority, or any other entity or organization. ProjectCo has the meaning given in the preamble. Prudent Utility Practices means those practices, methods, standards and acts engaged in or approved by a significant portion of the electric industry during the relevant time period, or any of the practices, methods and acts which, in the exercise of reasonable judgment in light of the facts known at the time the decision was made, could have been expected to accomplish the desired result at a reasonable cost consistent with good business practices, reliability, safety and expedition in a manner consistent with Applicable Laws, safety, environmental protection and economy. Prudent Utility Practices are not necessarily defined as the optimal standard practice method or act to the exclusion of others, but rather refer to a range of action reasonable under the circumstances and generally accepted in the region in connection with line taps and the ownership and operation of the facilities and arrangements described in this Agreement. PV Capacity means the interconnection use rights of the PV ProjectCo to use the Transmission Line to deliver the net output of the PV Facility to the Point of Interconnection pursuant to the LGIA, and other ancillary interconnection needs related to 24x7 auxiliary power, facility communications and other requirements necessary for performance under the LGIA, to the extent that the PV Facility is capable of producing and delivering energy to the Point of Interconnection. PV Capacity shall not include charging or delivery of battery stored energy. PV Capacity shall not include Deliverability rights and obligations as set forth in the LGIA. Substation means the meaning given in the Recitals. - 3 - Switchyard means the meaning given in the Recitals. Transmission Line has the meaning given in the Recitals.
ARTICLE 2 USE OF FACILITIES 2.1 Connection. GenTie Co will allow each ProjectCo to connect its Facility to the Transmission Line and will cooperate with each ProjectCo to effectuate such connection in accordance with Applicable Laws and Prudent Utility Practice. 2.2 Use of the Transmission Line. During the term of this Agreement, GenTie Co will allow each ProjectCo to use the Coincident Capacity of the Transmission Line to deliver the output of its Facility from the Switchyard to the Substation and to deliver electricity from a provider of station service from the Substation to the Switchyard. PV ProjectCos right to use the Transmission Line shall be limited to the PV Capacity of the PV Facility set forth in the recitals hereto. CL BESS ProjectCos right to use the Transmission Line shall be limited to the BESS Capacity of the BESS Facility set forth in the recitals hereto. Each ProjectCos right to use the Transmission Line is contingent on its ownership interest in GenTie Co. If a ProjectCo transfers a portion of its ownership interest in GenTie Co, then its rights to use the Transmission Line shall be reduced to a capacity equal to the number of Units (as defined in the GenTie Co LLCA) retained by such ProjectCo in GenTie Co. 2.3 Scheduling. No scheduling services are required for the service provided under this Agreement. Each ProjectCo shall make all necessary scheduling arrangements with Southern California Edison Company and/or the CAISO to accept its output at the Substation. 2.4 Availability. GenTie Co acknowledges that each ProjectCos rights to access and utilize its Coincident Capacity is essential to the administration, operation and maintenance of its Facility. GenTie Co shall comply at all times with the requirements of this Agreement, shall operate and maintain its Transmission Line in accordance with Prudent Utility Practices, and coordinate use of the Transmission Line and any outages as follows: (a) coordinate with the other Parties with respect to scheduling any planned outages of either Facility and the Transmission Line with the goal of scheduling planned outages during periods which minimize the impact on each Facilitys operations. (b) shall give notice to the other Parties as soon as possible of any unplanned outages of the Transmission Line and shall work to restore the Transmission Line to service as quickly as possible. (c) The ProjectCos shall adopt operating assumptions (the Operating Assumptions) that reflect the proposed charging and discharge behavior of the CL BESS ProjectCo in a manner that is consistent with its BESS Capacity, the terms and conditions of the LGIA, and the requirements and guidelines of CAISO, SCE, NERC and any other entity with authority over the operations of the ProjectCos. If required under the LGIA or by SCE or CAISO, the ProjectCos shall provide such Operating Assumptions to SCE and CAISO. For the - 4 - avoidance of doubt, the ProjectCos may operate at the same time, with the PV ProjectCo having priority pursuant to the terms set forth in the GenTieCo LLCA. (d) The ProjectCos shall direct any third-party providing operations and maintenance, scheduling or other services to perform in a manner consistent with the Operating Assumptions and the terms of this Agreement, including under any offtake agreement in which the offtaker controls the scheduling of the resource. (e) The CL BESS ProjectCo may use the Transmission Line to charge BESS Facility at any time without any limitation under this Agreement; provided, however, that the CL BESS ProjectCo shall limit its charging activities in accordance with the LGIA and the requirements and guidelines of CAISO, SCE, NERC and any other entity with authority over its operations. (f) The ProjectCos anticipate that the CL BESS ProjectCo will not often use the Transmission Line to discharge the BESS Facility in a manner that would cause the PV ProjectCo to curtail the PV Facility; provided, however, that: (i) no ProjectCo shall be obligated to take any action that could result in a violation of a CAISO or SCE tariff; (ii) each ProjectCo shall operate its Facility in accordance with all dispatch orders issued by the CAISO; (iii) the Parties acknowledge and agree that BESS Capacity includes Deliverability rights under the LGIA, which may result in CAISO directing the CL BESS ProjectCo to discharge the BESS Facility despite the PV ProjectCos rights to use its PV Capacity during such CAISO direction; and (iv) the CL BESS ProjectCo shall reimburse the PV ProjectCo for lost revenue and production tax credits as set forth in the GenTie Co LLCA. 2.5 Curtailment.
